         <head>
            <title>Witness Statement Provided by Mary Miles Minter</title>
            <date>February 7, 1922</date>
            <orgName>District Attorney</orgName>
         </head>
         <div>
            <byline>Cade Brennan</byline>

            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN:</speaker>
               <ab>How long have <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> known <persName
                     ref="william_taylor">Mr Taylor?</persName>
               </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>Minter:</speaker>
               <ab>Since <time>July of 1919</time> -- yes, that is correct.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>Doran:</speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="william_taylor">He</persName> has been your
                     <roleName>director</roleName> in pictures, has <persName ref="william_taylor"
                     >he</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>Minter:</speaker>
               <ab>Did <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> have occasion to call on
                     <persName ref="william_taylor">him</persName> at <placeName ref="taylors">his
                     residence</placeName> within <time>the last thirty days</time> prior to
                     <persName ref="taylor">his</persName> death? -- approximately thirty days?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>Just a moment, will you --</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN:</speaker>
               <ab>Let me change the question. When was the last time <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> called on <persName ref="taylor"
                     >him</persName> at <placeName ref="taylors">his residence?</placeName>
               </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>On the <date>23rd of December</date>.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Were <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> alone at that time or did
                  others accompany <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> to see <persName
                     ref="william_taylor">him</persName>? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> was alone. </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Was any one else there?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>no, not a soul. </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Was <persName ref="william_taylor">his</persName>
                  <persName ref="henry_peavey">valet, the colored man</persName>, there, do
                     <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName> know?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>Not that I know of.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab><time>Prior to that time</time>, was it <persName ref="mary_miles_minter"
                     >your</persName> habit to call on <persName ref="william_taylor">him</persName>
                  at <placeName ref="taylors">his residence</placeName> or had it been <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">your</persName> habit?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> couldn't call it a habit, but on
                  several occasions <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> did call upon
                     <persName ref="william_taylor">him</persName>, though never <time>as·1ate as
                     upon this occasion</time>.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Now,<time> on this last occasion</time>, what <time>time of the day or
                     night</time> was it that <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName>
                  called? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker> MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>May <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">l</persName> tell this in <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">my</persName> own way? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Yes, <persName>I</persName> would rather have <persName ref="mary_miles_minter"
                     >you</persName> tell it in <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">your</persName>
                  own way, if you will.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> am glad to. <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> am trying to answer as <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> would in court and <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">1</persName> don't like to do so.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN:</speaker>
               <ab>Just proceed, go ahead and tell it in <persName ref="mary_miles_minter"
                     >your</persName> own way.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> had gone to bed; <persName
                     ref="mary_miles_minter">I</persName> hadn't seen <persName ref="william_taylor"
                     >Mr Taylor</persName> in five months at the time -- three months, I know; three
                  months, and I just got to thinking about it and I decided I couldn't stand it any
                  longer. I was going to go up and tell him "goodbye. I got up and dressed, went
                  down to my grandmother's room and I said, "Mama, I am going over to say 'goodbye'
                  to Mr Taylor," and she advised me not to do it. She said it was too late: "Do you
                  know it is nearly twelve o'clock?" she said. I said, "Yes, sure, but I just must
                  do so," I said, "I realize that this is not the usual thing and I have never been
                  there so late, but I must do so, Mama. I am going to give him a letter in whioh I
                  have told him 'goodbye,"' She said, "All right, then, if you must. I would get up
                  and go with you, but I don't feel well enough," Mama often accompanied me on my
                  trips, which were not very many during the entire time that i knew him. So I went
                  over there and arrived at five minutes to twelve, I am strange about that, I am
                  rather queer about that, I think of the time; every time I was with him I would
                  say, "Well, this time yesterday I didn't see him and today I am with him," and
                  things like that. So I arrived at five minutes to twelve and left at twenty
                  minutes to one, and-- Do you wish me to tell you all that transpired?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN:</speaker>
               <ab>Never mind about that. </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>Did <persName ref="charlotte_shelbey">your mother</persName> go with <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">you</persName>? No;
                     <persName>Mama</persName> is <persName>my grandmother</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="mama_miles">Your grandmother</persName> didn't accompany you? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>No, she did not. </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab><persName>Your chauffeur</persName> drove you there? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>No, I drove myself in my little <objectName>car</objectName>, little
                  run-about.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>That was <date>December 23rd</date>? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>Yes, <date>December 23rd</date>.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>When was the last time you saw him prior to that? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>I couldn't give you the exact date, but I know it was at least three months and a
                  little over; it was over three months. </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>See him and meet him, to be with him? </ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER: </speaker>
               <ab>No; no, indeed. I passed him at <placeName>Lasky Studio</placeName> when I go over there. Sometimes I
                  have seen his car go down <placeName>Western Avenue</placeName>, but I hadn't seen him to speak to in
                  three months.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>As I understand it, you were sincerely in love with him?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>That is true.</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>Did you convey that feeling to him?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>Absolutely.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp>
               <speaker>DORAN: </speaker>
               <ab>You told him, did you?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp>
               <speaker>MINTER:</speaker>
               <ab>Absolutely. <persName ref="william_taylor">He</persName> loved <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">me</persName>; <persName ref="william_taylor">he</persName> told <persName ref="mary_miles_minter">me</persName> so.</ab>
            </sp>



